data.title: Greencrops, 4010 Green Forage Pea - Organic
data.description: Very effective Nitrogen and bio mass builder. 4010 peas are the best leafy forage peas for plowdown, producing over 40” of green mass in 10 weeks. Best practice is to allow three weeks before seeding following crops. Mow down and work into soil at flowering.

data.title: Swiss Chard, Eldorado
data.description: Improved Golden Sunrise. Fresh new colour for salad blends. Bright orange stalks and veins with contrasting dark green leaves. Can be used as full-grown bunches or as baby leaves in salads and braising mixes. Good frost tolerance. Matures at 45cm/18”. 32 days baby; 59 days bunching Pkt contains 100-120 sds.

data.title: Swiss Chard, Ruby Red
data.description: Excellent for baby leaves or bunching. Dark green, crumpled leaves with crimson stalks and veins. Sweet, mild flavour. Plants grow 18” high. Also known as rhubarb chard. 32 days baby; 59 days bunching Pkt contains 100-225 sds.

data.title: Beets, Early Wonder AC Strain
data.description: Our earliest non-hybrid variety. Produces a topshaped, blood-red root for all purposes. Tall green tops are good for bunching. 60 days Pkt contains 150-200 sds

data.title: Beets, Bull's Blood
data.description: The ultimate beet top. Dark red leaves and stems add colour and zest to salads and cooked top recipes. Beets are flat-globed and have alternating red-white zones. Tops are 10-12” in height and hold up well in the heat. 60 days Pkt contains 100-140 sds

data.title: Sorrel, Green de Belleville
data.description: R. acetosa All green strain with lemony taste. Perennial | Ht. 45cm/18” | 800-1000 sds/gm.

data.title: Dill, Bouquet
data.description: A tall dill producing many flowerheads. Annual | Ht. 120cm/48” | 450-500 sds/gm.

data.title: Cilantro, Santo Organic
data.description: Slow bolting selection producing broad, fresh green leaves on strong stems. Excellent for bunching. Organically grown seed. Annual | 50-100 sds/gm.

data.title: Cilantro, Santo
data.description: Slow bolting selection producing broad, fresh green leaves on strong stems. Excellent for bunching. Annual | 50-100 sds/gm.

data.title: Chervil, Brussels Winter Vertissimo
data.description: Anthriscus cerefolium Brussels Winter strain. A preferred selection with darker green leaves. Chervil is a delicate leaved herb that enhances the flavours of other herbs. It is one of the fine herbs used in French cooking. Best direct seeded and kept moist until growth is seen. Annual | Ht. 45cm/18” | 300-400 sds/gm.

data.title: Basil, Red Rubin Improved
data.description: Improved Dark Opal. Develops deep purple colour in less favourable conditions. Suitable for greenhouse growing. Great accent plant for containers. Interesting in salads. Annual | Ht. 40cm/16” | 400-700 sds/gm.

data.title: Greencrops, Buckwheat Organic
data.description: Fastest growing summer covercrop. Buckwheat out grows everything including weeds, making it a great short term smother crop. While buckwheat does not yield a large biomass, it is an excellent scavenger of phosphorus and potassium releasing it to the next crop.

data.title: Greens, Mizuna
data.description: Very prolific, bolt-tolerant green producing up to 200 stems with holly-like serrated leaves. Excellent in gourmet salads and stir-fries. Pkt contains 650-750 sds.

data.title: Greens, Komatsuna
data.description: Easy to grow. Upright, fresh green plant produces tender, mild stalks with dark green, rounded leaves. Good for salads and braising. Pkt contains 500-650 sds.

data.title: Greens, Garden Cress Peppergrass
data.description: Lepidium sativum Peppergrass. A quick growing, extra curly cress that is ready to eat in two weeks. Tasty on sandwiches or in salads. Pkt contains 1800-1950 sds.

data.title: Greens, Red Garnet Amaranth
data.description: Interesting red leaves with soft texture. Tolerant to hot and dry conditions. Used to brighten up salads. Pkt contains 1150-1250 sds.

data.title: Winter Radish, Red Arrow / China Rose
data.description: Long, rose-coloured roots with mild, white flesh for fall and winter use. Produces pink sprouts with a nice spicy flavour. 60 days Pkt contains 300-500 sds.

data.title: Winter Radish, Round Black Spanish
data.description: An excellent black-skinned variety with crisp, spicy white flesh. Up to 4” wide. Great keeper. 55 days Pkt contains 400-450 sds.

data.title: Peas, Oregon Sugar Pod II
data.description: Large, sweet pods. Produces heavy yields of 4½” long and ¾” wide flat pods. Large, 3-4ft vines protect tender pods from the sun. Also known as Ho-lan-dow. Developed by OSU. 63 days Pkt contains 135-150 sds.

data.title: Peas, Aladdin pvp
data.description: Excellent processing pea for canners. It produces high yields of 3” long pods with dark green, medium-sized peas concentrated in one or two pickings. Plants are semi-leafless and dwarf growing to 18-28” high depending on time of year. Aladdin is very heat tolerant so it can be grown as a summer pea in many areas. (HR:F/BLRV IR:PM/ PEMV) 67 days Pkt contains 150-175 sds.

data.title: Onions, Evergreen Long White Nebuka
data.description: Long, slim, white stems. Very hardy for overwintering. Little to no bulbing. 70 days Pkt contains 400-500 sds.

data.title: Fennel, Finnochio/Florence
data.description: Common fennel. Recommended for foliage use. Great in salad blends and microgreen mixes. 100 days. Pkt contains 150-300 sds.

data.title: Kohlrabi, White Vienna
data.description: Common kohlrabi with light green skin and white flesh. Best used for salad blends and microgreen mixes. 65-70 days Pkt contains 150-200 sds
